# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Arc: StoryBeginnings | Scene: SarahAndThomasSpeak
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "Some days had passed and Sarah had spend them trying to forget about Kate's visit to her bedroom."
    new "Some days had passed and Sarah had spend them trying to forget about Kate's visit to her bedroom."

    old "Her words of warning, her attempt to take her away from Castle Reinmeer, it had all been so very odd."
    new "Her words of warning, her attempt to take her away from Castle Reinmeer, it had all been so very odd."

    old "But Sarah had soon found that Kate had been too cryptic. Sarah couldn't afford to be distracted, speculating about what dangers might be out there."
    new "But Sarah had soon found that Kate had been too cryptic. Sarah couldn't afford to be distracted, speculating about what dangers might be out there."

    old "There were plenty of real dangers all around her."
    new "There were plenty of real dangers all around her."

    old "Having finished reviewing some of the weekly reports, Sarah found herself wandering the castle, ending up in the great hall."
    new "Having finished reviewing some of the weekly reports, Sarah found herself wandering the castle, ending up in the great hall."

    old "Sitting atop the stairs near the dais, she found her brother Thomas."
    new "Sitting atop the stairs near the dais, she found her brother Thomas."

    old "She observed him as she approached, and noticed that he did not notice her."
    new "She observed him as she approached, and noticed that he did not notice her."

    old "He might be in this room, but in his head, he was very far away."
    new "He might be in this room, but in his head, he was very far away."

    old "Already prone to overthinking, her brother had turned almost entirely inward following the coronation."
    new "Already prone to overthinking, her brother had turned almost entirely inward following the coronation."

    old "Only cheerful thoughts, I hope?"
    new "Only cheerful thoughts, I hope?"

    old "Thomas looked up, startled."
    new "Thomas looked up, startled."

    old "Huh?"
    new "Huh?"

    old "I said, I hope you're having cheerful thoughts."
    new "I said, I hope you're having cheerful thoughts."

    old "Ooh...sorry, I wasn't paying attention."
    new "Ooh...sorry, I wasn't paying attention."

    old "Sarah flattened her dress and set down next to her brother."
    new "Sarah flattened her dress and set down next to her brother."

    old "She poked him with her elbow."
    new "She poked him with her elbow."

    old "Come on Thomas, share with me. We promised we were going to get through this together. That means trusting me enough to let me into your head."
    new "Come on Thomas, share with me. We promised we were going to get through this together. That means trusting me enough to let me into your head."

    old "Thomas nodded, but still seemed to stare into the distance."
    new "Thomas nodded, but still seemed to stare into the distance."

    old "You're right..."
    new "You're right..."

    old "It's just, ever since the coronation, it's all gotten even worse."
    new "It's just, ever since the coronation, it's all gotten even worse."

    old "What has?"
    new "What has?"

    old "The expectations that people seem to have. They come up to me, asking me to weigh in on one problem after the other."
    new "The expectations that people seem to have. They come up to me, asking me to weigh in on one problem after the other."

    old "And it's not just that, but they're also...different with me..."
    new "And it's not just that, but they're also...different with me..."

    old "Different how?"
    new "Different how?"

    old "I used to know what people were about, you know? If they liked me, or didn't like me. But now, everyone is always smiling at me."
    new "I used to know what people were about, you know? If they liked me, or didn't like me. But now, everyone is always smiling at me."

    old "Thomas paused for a moment."
    new "Thomas paused for a moment."

    old "But, it's like, their smiles aren't real, and I can see it, you know?"
    new "But, it's like, their smiles aren't real, and I can see it, you know?"

    old "Sarah understood what her brother was getting at."
    new "Sarah understood what her brother was getting at."

    old "Ever since their father had died, it was true that more and more people seemed to want to ingratiate themselves with them."
    new "Ever since their father had died, it was true that more and more people seemed to want to ingratiate themselves with them."

    old "Where before they had just been the heirs to the throne, now Thomas was actually king, and it made all the difference."
    new "Where before they had just been the heirs to the throne, now Thomas was actually king, and it made all the difference."

    old "Sarah put an arm around her brother."
    new "Sarah put an arm around her brother."

    old "I know things are different, Thomas, and it will take some time to get used to it."
    new "I know things are different, Thomas, and it will take some time to get used to it."

    old "But we'll get through this, you and me. And whenever things get too much, remember that I'm here for you. Always."
    new "But we'll get through this, you and me. And whenever things get too much, remember that I'm here for you. Always."

    old "Thomas nodded, but the words didn't seem to affect him much."
    new "Thomas nodded, but the words didn't seem to affect him much."

    old "People come up to me and ask me to settle disputes between noble houses I've never even heard of, or make military decisions, as if I know anything about that stuff..."
    new "People come up to me and ask me to settle disputes between noble houses I've never even heard of, or make military decisions, as if I know anything about that stuff..."

    old "It's all just too much, and I just keep thinking about Dad, and how he would do everything better..."
    new "It's all just too much, and I just keep thinking about Dad, and how he would do everything better..."

    old "Sarah pulled her brother closer."
    new "Sarah pulled her brother closer."

    old "I miss him too, Thomas."
    new "I miss him too, Thomas."

    old "The two siblings sat in silence for a while."
    new "The two siblings sat in silence for a while."

    old "An idea came to Sarah."
    new "An idea came to Sarah."

    old "You know, Thomas, maybe the problem is that you're trying to do everything all at once. You're not giving yourself the time to learn how to be king."
    new "You know, Thomas, maybe the problem is that you're trying to do everything all at once. You're not giving yourself the time to learn how to be king."

    old "Well, you're comparing yourself to father, but he was king for more than thirty years. Of course you can't be as good as him overnight."
    new "Well, you're comparing yourself to father, but he was king for more than thirty years. Of course you can't be as good as him overnight."

    old "Thomas nodded, understanding what his sister was getting at."
    new "Thomas nodded, understanding what his sister was getting at."

    old "Father often told me about his earliest days, how he struggled with the same things you're talking about."
    new "Father often told me about his earliest days, how he struggled with the same things you're talking about."

    old "And he said, a good king knows when to lead and when to listen. Maybe the problem is that you're taking on too much all at once."
    new "And he said, a good king knows when to lead and when to listen. Maybe the problem is that you're taking on too much all at once."

    old "For the first time that day, Thomas looked directly at his sister."
    new "For the first time that day, Thomas looked directly at his sister."

    old "So what do I do? I can't just ignore these issues, can I?"
    new "So what do I do? I can't just ignore these issues, can I?"

    old "No, you can't, but we could add more people to the council. People who know about war, and know about the inner workings of the noble families."
    new "No, you can't, but we could add more people to the council. People who know about war, and know about the inner workings of the noble families."

    old "Who?"
    new "Who?"

    old "Lord Marion and Lord Varga."
    new "Lord Marion and Lord Varga."

    old "Sarah could see Thomas frown."
    new "Sarah could see Thomas frown."

    old "Really? You want to add Marion to the council?"
    new "Really? You want to add Marion to the council?"

    old "I know you don't like him, but you're not looking for friends. You're looking for someone who is good at what they do."
    new "I know you don't like him, but you're not looking for friends. You're looking for someone who is good at what they do."

    old "And Marion's family is one of the oldest in Rosanna, and he knows just about everyone. He could be a real help to us."
    new "And Marion's family is one of the oldest in Rosanna, and he knows just about everyone. He could be a real help to us."

    old "And Varga, he's proven himself in battle, I've heard people say he's a genius at war. With him on the council, you can learn everything he knows."
    new "And Varga, he's proven himself in battle, I've heard people say he's a genius at war. With him on the council, you can learn everything he knows."

    old "Rely on them for their skills, not their personalities."
    new "Rely on them for their skills, not their personalities."

    old "Thomas looked away and contemplated his sister's advice. After some time, he responded."
    new "Thomas looked away and contemplated his sister's advice. After some time, he responded."

    old "You're right. I don't have to like them, but if you say they're as good as they are, we can use all the help we can get."
    new "You're right. I don't have to like them, but if you say they're as good as they are, we can use all the help we can get."

    old "Sarah patted her brother on the back."
    new "Sarah patted her brother on the back."

    old "I'll draft the letters to extend the invitation to both of them."
    new "I'll draft the letters to extend the invitation to both of them."

    old "What if they say no?"
    new "What if they say no?"

    old "Sarah shrugged."
    new "Sarah shrugged."

    old "Then we'll just order their heads off."
    new "Then we'll just order their heads off."

    old "Sarah drew her hand across her throat, signalling decapitation. She added an exaggerated death sound for effect."
    new "Sarah drew her hand across her throat, signalling decapitation. She added an exaggerated death sound for effect."

    old "Thomas broke into laughter."
    new "Thomas broke into laughter."

    old "Sarah laughed along with her brother, but more than anything, she was happy to see him smile again."
    new "Sarah laughed along with her brother, but more than anything, she was happy to see him smile again."

    old "It reminded her that the brother she knew, the easy-going quick-to-laugh brother, was still in there, despite the trauma."
    new "It reminded her that the brother she knew, the easy-going quick-to-laugh brother, was still in there, despite the trauma."

    old "Not long after, a messenger arrived for Thomas."
    new "Not long after, a messenger arrived for Thomas."

    old "He opened the letter and read it. After, he sighed and stood up."
    new "He opened the letter and read it. After, he sighed and stood up."

    old "The work never ends."
    new "The work never ends."

    old "Sarah held onto his hand and gave it a quick squeeze."
    new "Sarah held onto his hand and gave it a quick squeeze."

    old "Thomas smiled, comforted by the gesture."
    new "Thomas smiled, comforted by the gesture."

    old "Sarah watched as her brother began to walk away, down one of the many hallways of Castle Reinmeer."
    new "Sarah watched as her brother began to walk away, down one of the many hallways of Castle Reinmeer."

    old "Though his shoulders still hung low, she hoped that his crown weighed a little less on him now."
    new "Though his shoulders still hung low, she hoped that his crown weighed a little less on him now."

